===Taiwan=== {{See also|Cinema of Taiwan}} * ''[[Crouching Tiger, Hidden Dragon]]'' ([[traditional Chinese]]ï¼{{lang|zh-hant|è¥èèé¾}}): is a 2000 [[Wuxia]] film directed by [[Ang Lee]] and co-produced by [[Taiwan]], [[China]] and the [[United States]]. The movie won over 40 awards. Including [[Academy Award for Best Foreign Language Film]](for Taiwan) and 3 other [[Academy Awards]]. Also, nominated for 6 other Academy Awards. The film grossed [[US]]$128 million in the United States and became the highest grossing foreign-language film in American history.
